recipeMethods.stepInstructions:
1. Preheat oven to 425 F degrees.

2. Place breaded chicken onto sheet tray and cook for 15 minutes. 
Ensure internal temperture is 165 F degrees and above.

3. Hold cooked chicken in warmer between 150F - 160F degrees until 
needed.

1. Cut torpedo in half lenghtwise.

2. Place 2 slice of Mozzarella cheese inside of the bottom half of the 
torpedo covering the whole lenght. each side of the ciabatta loaf.

3. Place marinara sauce on top of cheese.

4. Place shredded parmesan cheese on top of marinara sauce.

5. Then cut breaded chicken lengthwise and place on top of the 
marinara sauce. 

6. Place on impinger At 500 degrees for 1 minute and 25 seconds.

7. Remove from impinger place in deli wraping paper and server right 
away.
